@@TJvPanel.ArrangeSettings
Summary
  Enables and controls automatic layout of components on the panel
Description
  These settings control how components are arranged on the panel. For Example, put components on the
  panel, *without* carefully aligning them. Set the ArrangeSettings properties, e.g. set the
  BorderLeft, DistanceHorizontal. Then set the ArrangeSettings.AutoArrange to true and the controls
  will be arranged.
Note
  Only works with TWinControl descendents, so will not work with TLabel for instance.

  Excellent for automatically arranging buttons on a panel, when the panel is likely to be resized.

